  "prompt": "What are some things new employees should know going into their first day at AIG?",
  "response": "Welcome to AIG! Starting a new job can be both exciting and a bit overwhelming, but here are some key things to keep in mind for your first day:\n\n### Company Overview\n- **AIG's History and Mission:** AIG, or American International Group, is a global insurance company with roots dating back to 1919. It's important to familiarize yourself with the company's mission, values, and its role in the insurance industry.\n\n### First Day Essentials\n- **Dress Code:** AIG typically has a business casual dress code, but it's always best to err on the side of professionalism. If you're unsure, ask your HR contact for guidance.\n- **Arrival Time:** Aim to arrive a bit early to give yourself time to get settled. Punctuality is always appreciated.\n- **Documents:** Bring necessary documents such as identification, completed HR forms, and any paperwork you were asked to bring.\n\n### Orientation and Training\n- **Onboarding Program:** AIG usually has a structured onboarding program that includes an introduction to company policies, procedures, and an overview of benefits. Pay close attention and take notes.\n- **Training:** You may undergo specific job-related training. Be proactive in learning and ask questions if anything is unclear.\n\n### Office Culture\n- **Team Dynamics:** Take time to meet your colleagues and understand team dynamics. Building relationships early can help you integrate smoothly.\n- **Communication:** Effective communication is key. Familiarize yourself with the preferred communication channels (email, internal messaging systems, etc.).\n\n### Practical Tips\n- **Workspace:** Get comfortable with your workspace. Identify key areas like restrooms, break rooms, and emergency exits.\n- **Technology:** Ensure you have access to necessary tools, software, and equipment. Don't hesitate to ask for help if you encounter technical issues.\n- **Lunch and Breaks:** Learn about break policies and nearby lunch options if meals are not provided.\n\n### Company Policies\n- **Compliance and Ethics:** AIG places high importance on compliance and ethical behavior. Make sure you understand and adhere to these policies.\n- **Security:** Be aware of security protocols, especially regarding sensitive information and data protection.\n\n### Career Development\n- **Goals and Expectations:** Have a clear understanding of your job responsibilities and performance expectations. Discuss your initial goals with your manager.\n- **Growth Opportunities:** AIG offers various opportunities for career development. Stay informed about training programs and mentorship opportunities.\n\n### Additional Resources\n- **Employee Handbook:** Review the employee handbook for detailed information about company policies and procedures.\n- **Intranet:** Explore the company intranet for resources, announcements, and useful information.\n\nRemember, your first day is just the beginning. Stay curious, be proactive, and enjoy the journey at AIG!",
